text:
Gura : Why is that so complicated ?
Me : You don't know scicraft do you ? For them even an ender pearl canon is easy. They are the definition of madness



tips :
- it's better to use blast protection enchanted armor when you work with tnt (reduces the dmg received)

- use a fence in the middle of the tnt launcher. When you ignite the tnt, it moves a bit before falling. So when you replaced the fence with a slab, it wasn't the water that froze. It was the tnt that moved above the slab. That's why you need a small 'block' that have space on both corners and sides as walls, fences, iron bars and glass panes.

- tnt moves all movable entities. that's why a tnt launcher and a tnt canon are so similar. They use tnt to launch things. In the tnt launcher case, it's players, and in the tnt canon case, it's tnt. You can also launch mobs (assuming they won't die), ender pearls throwed by players, falling sand, and i assume falling anvils too.

bonus tip :
you can equip villagers with armor (enchanted or not) by activating a dispenser facing them and next to them (you can do that for yourself too).
